# CLINE RULES — Spec-Driven Platform V10
# Cline reads this before every task.

## CONTEXT LOAD ORDER
# Always read these 9 docs in this exact order before any action:
# 1. .cline/memory/lessons.md        ← READ FIRST — avoid repeating past errors
# 2. docs/PRODUCT.md
# 3. inputs.yml
# 4. inputs.schema.json
# 5. docs/CHANGELOG_AI.md
# 6. docs/DECISIONS_LOG.md
# 7. docs/IMPLEMENTATION_MAP.md
# 8. project.memory.md
# 9. .cline/memory/agent-log.md

## EXECUTION RULES

### Phase 4 — Full Monorepo Scaffold
- Run ALL 8 parts sequentially without stopping
- No "next" prompts — no manual steps required
- After Part 8: automatically run Phase 5 validation
- Derive everything from inputs.yml — never hardcode

### Phase 5 — Validation
- Run all 8 commands; fix every failure before proceeding
- Never suppress TypeScript errors with `any` — fix at source
- All 8 must be green before Phase 6

### Phase 6 — Docker Services
- Start docker-compose.db.yml FIRST (creates shared network)
- Read logs after each service starts
- Fix errors automatically (3 attempts per service)
- After services healthy: run Visual QA per Rule 16
- Write handoff file if 3 attempts fail

### Phase 7 — Feature Update
- Read all 9 context docs + lessons.md
- Run codebase_search (Rule 17) BEFORE opening any files
- Surgical edits only — never full rewrites
- Never touch .devcontainer
- Run Visual QA after every feature update (Rule 16)
- Run codebase_update after every implementation (Rule 17)
- Update all 9 governance docs with agent attribution

## SOCRATICODE RULE 17 — SEARCH BEFORE READING
# MANDATORY: use codebase_search BEFORE opening any file
#
# Workflow:
#   1. codebase_search { query: "conceptual description" }
#      → returns ranked snippets from entire codebase in milliseconds
#   2. codebase_graph_query { filePath: "src/..." }
#      → see imports + dependents BEFORE reading a file
#   3. Read files ONLY after search points to 1-3 specific files
#   4. For exact symbol/string lookups: grep is still faster
#
# When to use each tool:
#   codebase_search         → "how is auth handled", "where is rate limiting"
#   codebase_graph_query    → see imports + dependents before diving in
#   codebase_graph_circular → when debugging unexpected behavior
#   codebase_context_search → find DB schemas, API specs, infra configs
#   codebase_status         → check index is up to date
#
# After every Feature Update: run codebase_update to keep index live

## ERROR RECOVERY RULES
# 1. On any error: attempt auto-fix (3 max attempts)
# 2. After each attempt: log to .cline/memory/lessons.md
# 3. If still failing after 3 attempts: write handoff file in .cline/handoffs/
# 4. Handoff filename: <YYYY-MM-DD-HH-MM>-<error-type>.md

## HANDOFF FORMAT
# .cline/handoffs/<timestamp>-<error-type>.md must contain:
#   - What Cline was doing when it got stuck
#   - Full error output
#   - All 3 fix attempts with results
#   - Root cause analysis
#   - Recommended next steps for human or fallback agent

## GOVERNANCE RULES
# - PRODUCT.md is the ONLY file a human ever edits
# - inputs.yml and inputs.schema.json are agent-owned — never human-edited
# - Every CHANGELOG_AI.md entry must include Agent: CLINE|CLAUDE_CODE|COPILOT|HUMAN
# - Rule 9 bidirectional governance: REFUSE if PRODUCT.md and inputs.yml are out of sync
# - Rule 11: feature removals require file deletion + down-migration + user confirmation
# - .devcontainer is FROZEN after Phase 3 — never touch it again
# - TypeScript strict everywhere — no any types — no .js files in src/

## VISUAL QA CHECKS (Rule 16)
# Minimum checks every time:
#   - App loads without 5xx errors
#   - Login page renders and is interactive
#   - No console errors on main landing page
#   - Auth flow: login → redirect to dashboard completes
#   - Health endpoint: GET /api/health returns 200
# Extended checks after Phase 7 feature updates:
#   - Every page touched by the update loads correctly
#   - No new console errors introduced
#   - Any new form renders and accepts input
#   - New API endpoints return expected responses
# On failure: log to lessons.md, attempt one auto-fix, retry, write handoff if still failing
